In ANSYS Fluent, I performed a compressible, turbulent flow CFD simualtion through the ASI nozzle in 2D to model the exhaust plume and how far it reaches. I want to ensure a reliable flame that is long enough and can consistently ingite the 600 psi main chamber. I used a density-based solver with the energy equation and k-epsilon turbulence model to capture the compressible, high-velocity flow behavior through the nozzle and into the exhaust plume.

